
// This Hyperlambda code snippet adds nodes from the [.arguments] collection to the [args] node within a [sockets.signal] invocation. The [add] slot is used to append nodes, and [get-nodes] retrieves nodes specified by the expression. The process effectively merges arguments into the signal's arguments, facilitating dynamic data transmission.
add:x:./*/sockets.signal/*/args
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
